GateDocument.TextWithNodes: CALL FOR PAPERS International Workshop on Workflow Management WFM'98 August 28 , 1998 http : / / www . ifi . uni-klu . ac . at / wfm 98 in connection with the 9 th International Conference on Database and Expert Systems Applications DEXA'98 to be held in Vienna , August 24 - 28 , 1998 http : / / www . ifs . tuwien . ac . at / dexa 98 / and co-located with the 15 th IFIP World Computer Congress IFIP'98 to be held in Vienna and Budapest , August 31 - September 4 , 1998 http : / / www . ocg . or . at / ifip 98 . html Workshop proceedings to be published by IEEE Computer Society Press - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Outline : - - - - - - - - Workflow management systems are developed to support / automate the execution of business processes . A workflow systems enacts a business process by assigning tasks to workflow agents according to the workflow specification . In this workshop we will focus on the management of workflows . Management is an activity which has to do with planning , controlling , organizing , making decisions , and solving problems . Current workflow systems support the management of processes in different degrees . Many state-of-the-art workflow systems are mainly concerned with the routing and assignment of tasks and provide little support for the above mentioned managerial aspects . This workshop will provide a forum for the exchange of novell ideas on the following key questions : * How can workflow systems support the management of processes ? * How can workflows be managed ? Major topics of interest which address the above questions may include but are not limited to : Workflow Control Workflow Transactions Exception Handling in Workflow Systems Workflow Administration Time Management in Workflow Systems Management of Resources in Workflow Systems Workflow Monitoring Dynamic Workflows Workflow Planning and Control Systems Workflow reporting Data Mining in Workflow Systems Process Improvement Cycles Organizational Environment for Workflow Application Experiences in the Application of Workflow Systems Work Scheduling Workflow and Quality Management Cooperation between Workflow Management Systems and Groupware Systems Generation of Processes from Case Descriptions Workflow and Project Management Workflow Management and Personal Productivity Tools Program Committee Chair - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Johann Eder Department for Informatics- Systems University of Klagenfurt Universitaetsstr . 65 A- 9020 Klagenfurt , Austria email : eder @ vfu . rh . it Program Committee - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Clemens Beckstein , Germany Omran Bukresh , USA Asuman Dogac , Turkey Clarence "Skip" Ellis , USA Herbert Groiss , Austria Steff Joosten , Netherlands Gerti Kappel , Austria Nihan Kesim , Turkey Frank Leyman , Germany Amit Sheth , USA Submission Details - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Authors are invited to submit research contributions representing original , previously unpublished work . Submitted papers will be carefully evaluated based on originality , significance , technical soundness , and clarity of exposition . All papers will be refereed by three members of the program committee . Accepted papers will be published by IEEE Computer Society Press as proceedings of the DEXA'98 workshops . All submitted papers MUST be formatted according to the author guidelines provided by IEEE Computer Society Press and MUST NOT be longer than 4000 words in double space . We highly encourage electronic submission by email in the form of post-script file to wfm 98 @ vj . soc . xp In case you have problem in sending by email , please send four hard copies to the program commitee chair . IMPORTANT DATES * Submission of abstracts : March 10 , 1998 * Submission of full papers : March 17 , 1998 * Notification of acceptance : May 5 , 1998 * Camera-ready copies due : June 10 , 1998 The authors are requested to send the abstract of the paper in ASCII format including the paper title , keywords , author names , addresses , and affiliations , by email to wfm 98 @ vq . yy . igo For any further questions or inquiries please contact the program commitee chair . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
